Specifically, the following modules under scripts/lib/ adapt patterns from
codex-plugin-cc's plugins/codex/scripts/lib/:

- state.mjs    — bucket layout, slug + hash naming, job JSON I/O
                 (adapted from state.mjs)
- gc.mjs       — count + age based prune over terminal jobs
                 (adapted from state.mjs pruneJobs)
- capture.mjs  — turn-state machine, notification dispatch, reasoning dedup,
                 fileChange / commandExecution capture, subagent labeling
                 (adapted from codex.mjs captureTurn / applyTurnNotification)
- result.mjs   — brief / detail / result rendering, prefix-matched job id,
                 elapsed-duration formatting, log tail preview
                 (adapted from render.mjs / job-control.mjs)

The original Apache-2.0 license text and copyright notices are preserved in
each adapted file via SPDX headers and an attribution comment. No code from
codex-plugin-cc's broker / hooks / commands / render layers / rescue agent
is included in this skill.
